(698, 10, '2015-04-29 17:53:40', '2015-04-29 17:53:40', 'We at KoreConX believe that equity crowdfunding has become a game changer for all parties involved in an investment. Investors are no longer recognized just for their timely and essential help to the company – they can also reap profits by having a stake in the company. The presence of a virtually unlimited amount of equity crowdfunding websites and platforms has facilitated the origin of a brand new ecosystem which protects all parties involved in the process, and also provides an abundance of opportunities for different types of entrepreneurs to seek help from a variety of investors.\r\n\r\nWhile anybody can benefit from investing via an equity crowdfunding portal, from an entrepreneurs’ point of view, it is important that equity crowdfunding is seen to pave a way for a successful partnership. The term “partnership” is very important, because it emphasizes the inherent collaboration the entrepreneur needs to have with the investor. The entrepreneur may have invested all his time and financial resources, and even sacrificed his previous job to start this venture, but there may come a time when the entrepreneur seeks funds to further his venture, needs technical or strategic guidance to solve bigger or deep-rooted problems associated with his business, capital is stuck in overproduction of inventory, equipment is not commercialized (leading to inefficiency in production), or there is a problem with the business concept. In all of these situations, the entrepreneur dearly needs help from the outside to prevent his “baby” from failing. The last thing that an entrepreneur could think of would be to lose everything he has worked so hard for, and therefore, an equity crowdfunding deal can be advantageous to this entrepreneur, provided that it is sought for the right reasons and the partnership has resulted in the right fit between what the investor can bring to the table and what the entrepreneur needs in return.\r\n\r\nBased on the needs of an entrepreneur and the value that the investor brings, the equity of the company given to the investor can be decided. This too is risky for the entrepreneur, as giving too much equity could easily allow the investor to take control of the business, and similarly giving too little equity may drive the investor away, because they feel that they don’t have significant returns on their investment. In order to prepare for this, it is always a good idea to seek a valuation of the company from independent advisors. Based on this, the entrepreneur may give an appropriate amount of his company in return for the services he seeks.\r\n\r\nSometimes, however, a partnership does not result in a desirable position. This may happen either with one or many investors, but in the latter case, the position might become too complicated for an entrepreneur to deal with. Many investors, each of whom have their own vision of the company and their opinions about how to solve problems, might become challenging for the entrepreneur. In this case, the entrepreneur goes from focussing on the company to focussing on mediating the investors. He has to apply extra energy to make sure there is no confusion rather than applying this extra energy to removing the problem itself. The advantage that the entrepreneur has here is that he is still in control of his business, and he can take more investors in or buy back in the company and return the number of investors to one at which he feels comfortable.\r\n\r\nIn today’s business landscape, in which there are unlimited avenues via which to start a business, faster distribution channels, greater efficiency in production, reduced costs of maintaining a small scale business (from 150K in 2000 to 1500 in 2010 for a software company), greater commercialization, increased information sharing, and an attitude towards innovation and working for yourself to make it big rather than working a 9 to 5 job, equity crowdfunding is a dream come true for the entrepreneur. Anybody now holds the potential to start with literally nothing except an idea that meets a special market demand, and some capital from outside to become a millionaire if the business plan is executed properly. Equity crowdfunding has played a pivotal role in transforming average citizens into company CEOs. Apart from just financial and strategic guidance that the investment allows, equity crowdfunding also provides more subtle but equally powerful benefits. Some of these benefits include reducing risk, testing the market via pre-sell, validation of a concept, and finally, free PR. Once the idea or the concept is put to the test by bringing it to an equity crowdfunding platform, the entrepreneur not only seeks an investment, but he also sees the validity of his idea when other people come on board and believe in the idea in the same way he does. Putting the idea out there also means free marketing, and if the idea is very powerful and transformative, our digital and online social media ensures that the word gets spread fast. Within minutes, an entrepreneur can be connected to powerful investors, who may change the world of the company in a positive way with a phone call, or key pieces of insight that the entrepreneur was missing.', 'Advantages of equity crowdfunding: entrepreneurs’ point of view', '', 'draft', 'open', 'closed', '', 'advantages-of-equity-crowdfunding-entrepreneurs-point-of-view', '', '', '2015-05-11 07:26:48', '2015-05-11 07:26:48', '', 0, 'http://koreconx.com/?p=698', 0, 'post', '', 0),
